M||name|webapp-testing
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Toolkit for interacting w/ and testing local web applications using Playwright. Supports verifying frontend functionality, debugging UI behavior, capturing browser screenshots, and viewing browser logs.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||lice|Complete terms in LICENSE.txt
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[dv, nx, ts, architecture, vc, ap-rt, bd, tc]
M||tx|---
M|Web |tx|To tst local web applications, write native Python Playwright scripts.
M|Web |**He|
M|Web |it|`scripts/with_server.py` - Manages server lifecycle (supports multiple servers)
M|Web |tx|**Always run scripts w/ `--help` first** to see usage. DO NOT read the source until you try running the script first and find that a customized solution is abslutely necessary. These scripts can be very large and thus pollute your context window. They exist to be called directly as black-box scripts rather than ingested into your context window.
M|Deci|tx|```
M|Deci|tx|us task → Is it static HTML?
M|Deci|tx|├─ Yes → Read HTML file directly to identify selectors
M|Deci|tx|│         ├─ sc → Write Playwright script using selectors
M|Deci|tx|│         └─ Fails/Incomplete → Treat as dynamic (below)
M|Deci|tx|│
M|Deci|tx|└─ No (dynamic webapp) → Is the server already running?
M|Deci|├─ N|python scripts/with_server.py --help
M|Deci|tx|│        Then use the helper + write simplified Playwright script
M|Deci|tx|│
M|Deci|└─ Y|
M|Deci|tx|1. Navigate and wait for networkidle
M|Deci|tx|2. Take screenshot or inspect DOM
M|Deci|tx|3. Identify selectors from rendered state
M|Deci|tx|4. Execute actions w/ discovered selectors
M|Deci|tx|```
M|Exam|To s|
M|Exam|**Si|**
M|Exam|tx|```bash
M|Exam|tx|python scripts/with_server.py --server "npm run dv" --port 5173 -- python your_automation.py
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Exam|**Mu|**
M|Exam|tx|```bash
M|Exam|tx|python scripts/with_server.py \
M|Exam|tx|--server "cd backend && python server.py" --port 3000 \
M|Exam|tx|--server "cd frontend && npm run dv" --port 5173 \
M|Exam|tx|-- python your_automation.py
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Exam|To c|
M|Exam|tx|```python
M|Exam|tx|from playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright
M|Exam|with|
M|Exam|tx|browser = p.chromium.launch(headless=True) # Always launch chromium in headless mode
M|Exam|tx|page = browser.new_page()
M|Exam|page|//localhost:5173') # Server already running and ready
M|Exam|page|Wait for JS to execute
M|... |tx|browser.close()
M|... |tx|```
M|Reco|1. *|
M|Reco|tx|```python
M|Reco|tx|page.screenshot(path='/tmp/inspect.png', full_page=True)
M|Reco|tx|cn = page.cn()
M|Reco|tx|page.locator('button').all()
M|Reco|tx|```
M|Reco|tx|2. **Identify selectors** from inspection results
M|Reco|tx|3. **Execute actions** using discovered selectors
M|Comm|tx|❌ **Don't** inspect the DOM before waiting for `networkidle` on dynamic apps
M|Comm|tx|✅ **Do** wait for `page.wait_for_load_state('networkidle')` before inspection
M|Best|it|**Use bundled scripts as black boxes** - To accomplish a task, consider whether one of the scripts available in `scripts/` can help. These scripts handle common, complex workflows reliably w/o cluttering the context window. Use `--help` to see usage, then invoke directly.
M|Best|it|Use `sync_playwright()` for synchronous scripts
M|Best|it|Always close the browser when done
M|Best|- Us|`text=`, `role=`, CSS selectors, or IDs
M|Best|- Ad|`page.wait_for_selector()` or `page.wait_for_timeout()`
